# Help your students sign up for the AP CS Principles Exam

<img src="/images/csp-hof-2.png" width="100%"/>

AP CS Principles is all about changing the face of computer science. With an explicit emphasis on broadening participation by girls and students of color, the course has done just that with <a href="https://www.collegeboard.org/releases/2019/participation-csp-nearly-doubles", target=_"blank">record setting growth</a> since its lauch in 2017!

But did you know that girls and students of color are less likely to take the AP exam? While the total number of women and students from historically underrepresented minorites in AP computer science has grown ten-fold since 2013, many students won’t get credit for their work at the college level because they don’t take the exam.  

**That's where YOU come in.** Teachers and parents are key to motivating students to try the exam. Join the 350+ teachers at schools in our [AP CS Principles Hall of Fame](/educate/csp/hall-of-fame) who have helped lead record-breaking change in computer science by encouraging girls and underrepresented minorities in their classrooms.

